* All of the diphthongs are falling.
* {{IPA|/eɪ, øʏ, oʊ/}} used to be pronounced as monophthongs {{IPA|[eː, øː, oː]}},{{sfnp|Hinskens|Taeldeman|2013|p=167}} a realization which is rapidly regaining popularity among younger speakers.
* Traditionally, {{IPA|/ɔu/}} used to have such a close first element that there was practically no distinction between {{IPA|/ɔu/}} and {{IPA|/oʊ/}}.
* Phonetically, {{IPA|/ɔːə/}} can be either {{IPA|[ɔːə]}} or {{IPA|[ɔːɑ]}}.

